RNASeq analysis

Mangalangi Udayakumar

15.07.2025

Introduction

The aim of this RNA-seq analysis is to develop skills in multi-omic data integration and analysis. This study focuses on identifying genes that are differentially expressed across experimental conditions in the yeast dataset.

Methods

The RNA-seq analysis was performed using a reproducible workflow managed by Snakemake, which automated steps from raw data download to quantification and initial quality control.

  • Data Acquisition and Quality Control:
    Raw FASTQ files were downloaded from NCBI SRA (GSE88952) using fasterq-dump (SRA Toolkit v3.2.1). Reads underwent quality assessment with FastQC (v0.12.1). Summary reports were aggregated using MultiQC (v1.11).

  • Read Alignment:
    Quality-checked reads were aligned to the Saccharomyces cerevisiae sacCer3 reference genome using HISAT2 (v2.2.1). The genome index was built with the corresponding gene annotation file derived from the Saccharomyces cerevisiae R64-1-1 assembly (SGD, last updated October 2018; genome build accession GCA_000146045.2), which is compatible with the sacCer3 genome.

  • Gene Quantification:
    Gene-level counts were generated using featureCounts (v2.1.1), specifying paired-end mode and strand-specificity as appropriate for the dataset.

  • Differential Expression Analysis:
    Differential expression was assessed with DESeq2 (v1.38.3) in R (v4.2.2). The Snakemake pipeline executed up to the count matrix generation, while DESeq2 analyses (including PCA, volcano plots, heatmaps) were performed with custom R scripts.

  • Downstream Analyses and Visualization:

    • Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (GSEA) using fgsea (v1.24.0).
    • Heatmaps with pheatmap (v1.0.13).
    • Volcano plots with EnhancedVolcano (v1.16.0).
    • Genome coverage tracks visualized using IGV after BigWig generation with deepTools (v3.5.6).

  • Environment and Computational Resources:
    Analyses were conducted on a Debian-based virtual machine (2 CPUs, 8 GB RAM). Separate Conda environments were maintained for each pipeline step, ensuring reproducibility with pinned dependencies (documented in accompanying YAML files).

All steps were designed for modular execution within limited-resource environments.

Appendix: Snakemake Workflow Files

Snakefile_1

###############################################
# Snakefile_1: RNA-seq download + QC
# Location: /media/sf_Shared/yeast_pipeline
###############################################

import pandas as pd

# === Load samples.tsv ===
SAMPLES_TSV = "config/samples.tsv"
sample_table = pd.read_csv(SAMPLES_TSV, sep="\t")

# === Filter RNA-seq samples ===
rna_samples = sample_table[sample_table["type"] == "rna"]
RNA_SAMPLES = rna_samples["sample"].tolist()
SAMPLE_TO_SRR = dict(zip(rna_samples["sample"], rna_samples["srr"]))

# === Paths ===
BASE = "/media/sf_Shared/yeast_pipeline"
RAW = f"{BASE}/data/raw"
QC_FASTQC = f"{BASE}/qc/fastqc"
QC_MULTIQC = f"{BASE}/qc/multiqc"
ALIGNMENTS = f"{BASE}/alignments"
HISAT2_INDEX = f"{BASE}/genome/sacCer3"
QC_MULTIQC_ALIGN = f"{BASE}/qc/multiqc_alignment"
COUNTS = f"{BASE}/counts"
METADATA = f"{BASE}/metadata"
RESULTS = f"{BASE}/results"

# === FINAL TARGET ===
rule all:
    input:
        expand(f"{RAW}/{{sample}}_1.fastq.gz", sample=RNA_SAMPLES),
        expand(f"{RAW}/{{sample}}_2.fastq.gz", sample=RNA_SAMPLES),
        expand(f"{QC_FASTQC}/{{sample}}_1_fastqc.zip", sample=RNA_SAMPLES),
        expand(f"{QC_FASTQC}/{{sample}}_2_fastqc.zip", sample=RNA_SAMPLES),
        f"{QC_MULTIQC}/multiqc_report.html",
        expand(f"{ALIGNMENTS}/{{sample}}.sorted.bam", sample=RNA_SAMPLES),
        expand(f"{ALIGNMENTS}/{{sample}}.flagstat.txt", sample=RNA_SAMPLES),
        f"{QC_MULTIQC_ALIGN}/multiqc_report.html",
        "counts/gene_counts.tsv",
        f"{RESULTS}/deseq2_results.csv",
        f"{RESULTS}/pca_plot.png",
        f"{RESULTS}/volcano_plot.png",
        f"{RESULTS}/heatmap.png",
        f"{RESULTS}/top_DE_genes.csv",
        f"{RESULTS}/normalized_counts.csv",
        f"{RESULTS}/volcano_labeled.png",

# === Download and compress with pigz ===
rule download_fastq:
    output:
        r1 = f"{RAW}/{{sample}}_1.fastq.gz",
        r2 = f"{RAW}/{{sample}}_2.fastq.gz"
    params:
        srr = lambda wc: SAMPLE_TO_SRR[wc.sample]
    shell:
        """
        mkdir -p {RAW}
        fasterq-dump --split-files {params.srr} --threads 2 -O {RAW}
        pigz -p 2 {RAW}/{params.srr}_1.fastq
        pigz -p 2 {RAW}/{params.srr}_2.fastq
        mv {RAW}/{params.srr}_1.fastq.gz {output.r1}
        mv {RAW}/{params.srr}_2.fastq.gz {output.r2}
        """

# === FastQC ===
rule fastqc:
    input:
        r1 = f"{RAW}/{{sample}}_1.fastq.gz",
        r2 = f"{RAW}/{{sample}}_2.fastq.gz"
    output:
        r1_html = f"{QC_FASTQC}/{{sample}}_1_fastqc.html",
        r1_zip = f"{QC_FASTQC}/{{sample}}_1_fastqc.zip",
        r2_html = f"{QC_FASTQC}/{{sample}}_2_fastqc.html",
        r2_zip = f"{QC_FASTQC}/{{sample}}_2_fastqc.zip"
    shell:
        """
        mkdir -p {QC_FASTQC}
        fastqc {input.r1} {input.r2} --outdir {QC_FASTQC}
        """

# === MultiQC ===
rule multiqc:
    input:
        expand(f"{QC_FASTQC}/{{sample}}_1_fastqc.zip", sample=RNA_SAMPLES),
        expand(f"{QC_FASTQC}/{{sample}}_2_fastqc.zip", sample=RNA_SAMPLES)
    output:
        f"{QC_MULTIQC}/multiqc_report.html"
    shell:
        """
        mkdir -p {QC_MULTIQC}
        multiqc {QC_FASTQC} -o {QC_MULTIQC}
        """

# === hisat2_align ===
rule hisat2_align:
    input:
        r1 = f"{RAW}/{{sample}}_1.fastq.gz",
        r2 = f"{RAW}/{{sample}}_2.fastq.gz",
        idx = expand("{idx}.{i}.ht2", idx=HISAT2_INDEX, i=range(1, 9))
    output:
        bam = f"{ALIGNMENTS}/{{sample}}.sorted.bam"
    log:
        f"{ALIGNMENTS}/{{sample}}.log"
    threads: 2
    shell:
        """
        mkdir -p {ALIGNMENTS}
        hisat2 -p {threads} -x {HISAT2_INDEX} \
            -1 {input.r1} -2 {input.r2} \
            | samtools sort -@ {threads} -o {output.bam}
        samtools index {output.bam}
        """

# === samtools_flagstat ===
rule samtools_flagstat:
    input:
        bam = f"{ALIGNMENTS}/{{sample}}.sorted.bam"
    output:
        txt = f"{ALIGNMENTS}/{{sample}}.flagstat.txt"
    shell:
        """
        samtools flagstat {input.bam} > {output.txt}
        """

# === multiqc_alignment ===
rule multiqc_alignment:
    input:
        logs = expand(f"{ALIGNMENTS}/{{sample}}.flagstat.txt", sample=RNA_SAMPLES)
    output:
        html = f"{QC_MULTIQC_ALIGN}/multiqc_report.html"
    shell:
        """
        mkdir -p {QC_MULTIQC_ALIGN}
        multiqc {ALIGNMENTS} -o {QC_MULTIQC_ALIGN}
        """
# === featurecounts ===
rule featurecounts:
    input:
        bams = expand(f"{ALIGNMENTS}/{{sample}}.sorted.bam", sample=RNA_SAMPLES),
        annotation = "genome/yeast.gtf"
    output:
        tsv = "counts/gene_counts.tsv"
    threads: 2
    conda:
        "envs/subread.yaml"
    shell:
        """
        mkdir -p counts
        featureCounts -T {threads} -p -a {input.annotation} -o {output.tsv} {input.bams}
        """
# === deseq2 ===
rule deseq2:
    input:
        counts = f"{COUNTS}/gene_counts.tsv",
        meta = f"{BASE}/metadata/samples.csv"
    output:
        results = [
            f"{RESULTS}/deseq2_results.csv",
            f"{RESULTS}/pca_plot.png",
            f"{RESULTS}/volcano_plot.png",
            f"{RESULTS}/heatmap.png",
            f"{RESULTS}/dds.rds"
        ]
    conda:
        "/home/mangalangi/envs/deseq2_env" 
    shell:
        """
        mkdir -p {RESULTS}
        Rscript scripts/run_deseq2.R {input.counts} {input.meta} {output[0]} {output[1]} {output[2]} {output[3]}
        """

# === deseq2_export ===
rule deseq2_export:
    input:
        rds = f"{RESULTS}/dds.rds",
        res = f"{RESULTS}/deseq2_results.csv"
    output:
        top_genes = f"{RESULTS}/top_DE_genes.csv",
        norm_counts = f"{RESULTS}/normalized_counts.csv",
        volcano_highlight = f"{RESULTS}/volcano_labeled.png"
    conda:
        "/home/mangalangi/envs/deseq2_env"
    shell:
        """
        Rscript scripts/export_top_genes.R {input.rds} {input.res} {output.top_genes} {output.norm_counts} {output.volcano_highlight}
        """

Appendix: Custom R Scripts Used

run_deseq2.R

#!/usr/bin/env Rscript

# Load libraries
suppressMessages({
  library(DESeq2)
  library(pheatmap)
  library(EnhancedVolcano)
  library(ggplot2)
})

# Read command-line arguments
args <- commandArgs(trailingOnly = TRUE)
if (length(args) != 6) {
  stop("Usage: Rscript run_deseq2.R <counts.tsv> <samples.csv> <output.csv> <pca.png> <volcano.png> <heatmap.png>")
}

counts_file <- args[1]
meta_file   <- args[2]
out_csv     <- args[3]
out_pca     <- args[4]
out_volcano <- args[5]
out_heatmap <- args[6]

# Load data
counts <- read.delim(counts_file, comment.char = "#", row.names = 1)
meta   <- read.csv(meta_file, row.names = 1)

# Extract counts only (assumes 6-column featureCounts output)
counts <- counts[, 6:ncol(counts)]
colnames(counts) <- rownames(meta)

# DESeq2
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = counts, colData = meta, design = ~ condition)
dds <- DESeq(dds)
res <- results(dds)
write.csv(as.data.frame(res), file = out_csv, row.names = TRUE )

# PCA
vsd <- vst(dds, blind = FALSE)
p <- plotPCA(vsd, intgroup = "condition")
ggsave(out_pca, plot = p, width = 6, height = 5)

# Volcano
png(out_volcano, width = 800, height = 600)
EnhancedVolcano(res,
                lab = rownames(res),
                x = "log2FoldChange",
                y = "pvalue",
                title = "Volcano Plot")
dev.off()

# Heatmap
top_genes <- head(order(res$padj, na.last = NA), 30)
mat <- assay(vsd)[top_genes, ]
pheatmap(mat, scale = "row", show_rownames = TRUE,
         annotation_col = meta, filename = out_heatmap)

# Save DESeq2 object for downstream export
saveRDS(dds, file = "results/dds.rds")

fgsea_updated.R

library(fgsea)
library(data.table)
library(ggplot2)

# Load ranked gene list (mapped Ensembl → Symbol)
rnk <- fread("results/deseq2_ranked_mapped.rnk", header = FALSE)
ranks <- setNames(rnk$V2, rnk$V1)  # Named vector

# Load gene sets
gene_sets <- gmtPathways("data/yeast_go_bp.gmt")

# Run GSEA
set.seed(42)
fgseaRes <- fgsea(
  pathways = gene_sets,
  stats = ranks,
  minSize = 10,
  maxSize = 500,
  nperm = 10000
)

# Filter significant
fgsea_sig <- fgseaRes[padj < 0.05][order(padj)]

# Save results
fwrite(fgseaRes, "results/fgsea_all_results.tsv", sep = "\t")
fwrite(fgsea_sig, "results/fgsea_significant_results.tsv", sep = "\t")

# Plot top 10 enriched pathways
library(ggplot2)
top_n <- 10
ggplot(head(fgsea_sig, top_n), aes(reorder(pathway, NES), NES)) +
  geom_col(fill = "darkorange") +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(
    x = "Pathway",
    y = "Normalized Enrichment Score",
    title = "Top Enriched GO Biological Process Pathways"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

# Save barplot
ggsave("figures/fgsea_barplot_top10.png", width = 7, height = 5)

# Plot enrichment curve for top pathway
top_path <- fgsea_sig$pathway[1]
plotEnrichment(gene_sets[[top_path]], ranks) +
  labs(title = top_path)

ggsave("figures/fgsea_enrichment_top1.png", width = 7, height = 5)

save_enrichment_plots.R

# Required packages
library(fgsea)
library(data.table)
library(ggplot2)

# === Load ranked gene list ===
rnk_file <- "results/deseq2_ranked.rnk"
rnk_df <- fread(rnk_file, header = FALSE)
ranks <- setNames(rnk_df$V2, rnk_df$V1)

# === Load gene sets ===
gene_sets <- gmtPathways("data/yeast_go_bp.gmt")

# === Load fgsea results ===
fgsea_results <- fread("results/fgsea_results.tsv")
sig_fgsea <- fgsea_results[padj < 0.05]

# === Create output directory ===
dir.create("results/enrichment_plots", showWarnings = FALSE)

# Filter out rows with NA pathway names BEFORE the loop
sig_fgsea <- sig_fgsea[!is.na(pathway)]

# Loop through cleaned pathways
for (i in 1:nrow(sig_fgsea)) {
  pathway_name <- sig_fgsea$pathway[i]
  
  # Safe check for NA or blank name
  if (isTRUE(is.na(pathway_name)) || pathway_name == "") {
    message(" Skipping invalid pathway name at row ", i)
    next
  }
  
  if (pathway_name %in% names(gene_sets)) {
    genes <- gene_sets[[pathway_name]]
    
    file_safe <- gsub("[^A-Za-z0-9_]", "_", pathway_name)
    out_path <- paste0("results/enrichment_plots/", file_safe, ".png")
    
    png(out_path, width = 1000, height = 600)
    print(plotEnrichment(genes, ranks) + ggtitle(pathway_name))
    dev.off()
    
    message(" Saved: ", pathway_name)
    
  } else {
    message(" Skipping unmatched pathway: ", pathway_name)
  }
}

## ----igv_snapshots_by_pathway, echo=FALSE, results='asis', message=FALSE, warning=FALSE----

# Define pathways and leading edge genes
pathway_images <- list(
  "GOBP_CHROMOSOME_ORGANIZATION" = c("DMC1", "HOP1", "MND1", "HOP2", "MSH4"),
  "GOBP_PHOSPHORUS_METABOLIC_PROCESS" = c("CDC19", "ENO2", "GPM1", "PGK1", "TPI1"),
  "GOBP_SMALL_MOLECULE_METABOLIC_PROCESS" = c("CDC19", "ENO2", "GPM1", "PGK1", "TPI1")
)

# Initialize output
output_lines <- character()
use_latex <- knitr::is_latex_output()

for (pathway in names(pathway_images)) {
  output_lines <- c(output_lines, paste0("### ", pathway, "\n"))
  
  for (gene in pathway_images[[pathway]]) {
    img_path <- file.path("igv_snapshots", paste0(pathway, "_", gene, ".png"))
    
    if (file.exists(img_path)) {
      if (use_latex) {
        output_lines <- c(output_lines,
          paste0("\\begin{figure}[H]\n\\centering\n\\includegraphics[width=0.8\\textwidth]{", img_path, "}\n\\caption{", gene, "}\n\\end{figure}\n")
        )
      } else {
        output_lines <- c(output_lines,
          paste0('<img src="', img_path, '" width="600px" style="display:block; margin-bottom:15px;" />')
        )
      }
    } else {
      output_lines <- c(output_lines, paste0("*Image missing for ", gene, " in ", pathway, "*\n"))
    }
  }
  
  output_lines <- c(output_lines, "\n")
}

knitr::asis_output(paste(output_lines, collapse = "\n"))


## ----appendix_snakemake_files, echo=FALSE, results='asis'-------------------
# Windows-style paths
snakefile_path <- "C:/Shared/yeast_pipeline/Snakefile_1"
rules_dir <- "C:/Shared/yeast_pipeline/rules"
config_path <- "C:/Shared/yeast_pipeline/config.yaml"
envs_dir <- "C:/Shared/yeast_pipeline/envs"

# Function to print code blocks with language highlighting
include_code_block <- function(file_path, lang = "python") {
  if (file.exists(file_path)) {
    cat("###", basename(file_path), "\n\n")
    cat(paste0("```", lang, "\n"))
    cat(readLines(file_path), sep = "\n")
    cat("\n```\n\n")
  } else {
    cat("**File not found:**", file_path, "\n\n")
  }
}

# Start Appendix
cat("# Appendix: Snakemake Workflow Files\n\n")

# Snakefile_1
include_code_block(snakefile_path)

# Rules directory (.smk)
if (dir.exists(rules_dir)) {
  rule_files <- list.files(rules_dir, pattern = "\\.smk$", full.names = TRUE)
  for (f in rule_files) {
    include_code_block(f)
  }
}

# Config.yaml
include_code_block(config_path, lang = "yaml")

# Conda env files (.yml / .yaml)
if (dir.exists(envs_dir)) {
  env_files <- list.files(envs_dir, pattern = "\\.ya?ml$", full.names = TRUE)
  for (f in env_files) {
    include_code_block(f, lang = "yaml")
  }
}

# Function to include code blocks
include_code_block <- function(file_path, lang = "r") {
  if (file.exists(file_path)) {
    cat("###", basename(file_path), "\n\n")
    cat(paste0("```", lang, "\n"))
    cat(readLines(file_path), sep = "\n")
    cat("\n```\n\n")
  } else {
    cat("**File not found:**", file_path, "\n\n")
  }
}

# Start the appendix section
cat("# Appendix: Custom R Scripts Used\n\n")

for (script in script_files) {
  include_code_block(file.path(scripts_dir, script))
